race.comment: The second division of the BM70 is also very deep with quite a few winning chances. Victorian visitor NEPRAVDA (11) has been scratched from SA recently but if she makes the trip this weekend, she will be hard to beat. She has tactical speed and the drop back to 1200m suits. In an open race, she can win or go very close. ZOUPURRING (2) will appreciate getting back to the big Morphettville track after getting back and failing to make an impact on the Parks track in a race that was dominated closer to the speed. He can also settle closer from barrier four and be right in the firing line in the last 200m. NICISH (10) found form last start and can hold it. She's another that maps to get a lovely run just behind the speed. DANCING STORM (4) hasn't done much wrong this campaign, albeit he needs to find that killer punch. Include him in the quaddie, as well as last-start winner HYPERNOVA (7) who can continue his good form.
